cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.CL

The paper presents an agent-based model for binary classification of textual documents, which involves machine learning and natural language processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the model for biomedical text classification, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
